Okay, just for easier copy/pasting, the functions would be (untested):
```python
def log_softmax(x):
    xdev = x - x.max(1, keepdims=True)
    return xdev - T.log(T.sum(T.exp(xdev), axis=1, keepdims=True))

def categorical_crossentropy_logdomain(log_predictions, targets):
    return -T.sum(targets * log_predictions, axis=1)
```
Note that the latter doesn't support `targets` being an int vector now, that would be `log_predictions[targets]` instead.

