Oh, noticed something interesting from the compatibility tests (which I assume were also failing before this change? @schoen ?)

```
server {
    server_name test.org;
}
```

When we deploy, we add `listen 443` here. Before, we would add the if statement to the block, which was definitely wrong. Now, we don't add it to this block at all. We should really be adding both a `listen 80` and the if statement here during redirect enhancement.

A hacky way to fix this is when we add `listen 443` to blocks with no listen directives, also add `listen 80`. I don't think this would be wrong? Because the statement was technically there, just implicit before?

The least hacky way would be to set up that mapping system, note that it previously had no listen directives, and then add this vhost into the list of vhosts we test for matchingness (which it will almost 100% certainly win I think so actually we could then just keep a note to enhance this one if we're asked later).

